It would be great to be able to pass arguments to Daemonize() - actually this prevents me from using it in a project.

```
def main(*args, **kwargs):
    while 1:
        doSomething(*args, **kwargs)

daemon = Daemonize(
    action='main', args=('foo','bar',), kwargs={'foo':'bar'}
)
daemon.start()
```
